picture is worth a thousand

00:01:51.110 --> 00:01:53.750 align:middle line:84%
words," and I've
found this to be true.

00:01:53.750 --> 00:01:57.050 align:middle line:10%
In the science of
cymatics, where

00:01:57.050 --> 00:02:00.020 align:middle line:10%
vibration is pumped
into a medium

00:02:00.020 --> 00:02:03.140 align:middle line:10%
so that the medium
displays a pattern,

00:02:03.140 --> 00:02:06.440 align:middle line:10%
a pictorial representation
of that vibration,

00:02:06.440 --> 00:02:08.300 align:middle line:10%
it tells us something
very interesting

00:02:08.300 --> 00:02:12.268 align:middle line:10%
about the way that nature
brings about change

00:02:12.268 --> 00:02:14.060 align:middle line:10%
and the that nature
brings about evolution.

00:02:14.060 --> 00:02:16.880 align:middle line:84%
So let me just share it
briefly with our audience.

00:02:16.880 --> 00:02:20.067 align:middle line:84%
If you're not familiar
with this, in the 1990s,

00:02:20.067 --> 00:02:20.900 align:middle line:90%
there was a science.

00:02:20.900 --> 00:02:22.190 align:middle line:90%
It is called cymatics.

00:02:22.190 --> 00:02:26.330 align:middle line:84%
C-Y-M-A-T-I-C-S. Hans
Jenny, Dr. Hans Jenny,

00:02:26.330 --> 00:02:28.790 align:middle line:84%
was the scientist that
brought this forward.

00:02:28.790 --> 00:02:31.370 align:middle line:84%
And what he did was,
he took a medium.

00:02:31.370 --> 00:02:32.540 align:middle line:90%
Sometimes it was liquid.

00:02:32.540 --> 00:02:35.180 align:middle line:90%
Sometimes it was a powder.

00:02:35.180 --> 00:02:38.510 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes it was a very
viscous liquid, like mercury.

00:02:38.510 --> 00:02:40.760 align:middle line:90%
He put it in a specialized dish.

00:02:40.760 --> 00:02:43.880 align:middle line:84%
And into this dish, he
would pump a vibration,

00:02:43.880 --> 00:02:45.990 align:middle line:90%
a very specific frequency.

00:02:45.990 --> 00:02:48.620 align:middle line:84%
And as the frequency would
increase or decrease,

00:02:48.620 --> 00:02:51.230 align:middle line:84%
a pattern would appear
in the dish that

00:02:51.230 --> 00:02:53.170 align:middle line:90%
correlated with that frequency.

00:02:53.170 --> 00:02:55.070 align:middle line:84%
And the reason this
is important is

00:02:55.070 --> 00:02:58.550 align:middle line:84%
because it gives us a really
powerful insight into way

00:02:58.550 --> 00:03:02.060 align:middle line:84%
that nature evolves
and accommodates

00:03:02.060 --> 00:03:03.630 align:middle line:90%
change in our world.

00:03:03.630 --> 00:03:06.500 align:middle line:84%
And what our audiences have
really found to be fascinating

00:03:06.500 --> 00:03:07.430 align:middle line:90%
is this--

00:03:07.430 --> 00:03:10.370 align:middle line:84%
we see these beautifully
complex patterns

00:03:10.370 --> 00:03:14.170 align:middle line:84%
look like flower petals and
sacred geometric designs.

00:03:14.170 --> 00:03:17.150 align:middle line:10%
And they are only sustainable
for a brief period of time.

00:03:17.150 --> 00:03:21.290 align:middle line:10%
And as the frequency
increases, those patterns,

00:03:21.290 --> 00:03:25.880 align:middle line:10%
they give way to a higher order,
to a more complex pattern.

00:03:25.880 --> 00:03:29.180 align:middle line:10%
However, to get there, the
whole thing has to break down.

00:03:29.180 --> 00:03:31.910 align:middle line:84%
Chaos giving way
to a higher order.

00:03:31.910 --> 00:03:35.990 align:middle line:84%
Now, I use this to illustrate to
people the very powerful image

00:03:35.990 --> 00:03:38.180 align:middle line:84%
of what is happening
in our lives

00:03:38.180 --> 00:03:40.517 align:middle line:84%
and what's happening
in our world today.

00:03:40.517 --> 00:03:42.350 align:middle line:10%
And I know you've seen
these images as well.

00:03:42.350 --> 00:03:43.760 align:middle line:10%
Do you think that's a
good representation?

00:03:43.760 --> 00:03:45.770 align:middle line:10%
Do we need the chaos to
get to a higher order?

00:03:45.770 --> 00:03:47.050 align:middle line:10%
>>LIPTON: Well, absolutely.

00:03:47.050 --> 00:03:49.180 align:middle line:10%
And let's separate
chaos from random.

00:03:49.180 --> 00:03:51.980 align:middle line:10%
Random means things are
just happening by accident.

00:03:51.980 --> 00:03:53.030 align:middle line:90%
You have no idea.

00:03:53.030 --> 00:03:56.000 align:middle line:84%
Chaos has a pattern, but
it's below our ability

00:03:56.000 --> 00:03:57.760 align:middle line:90%
to see the details.

00:03:57.760 --> 00:04:00.270 align:middle line:84%
So it looks random
on the surface,

00:04:00.270 --> 00:04:01.970 align:middle line:84%
but if you understood
what was going on,

00:04:01.970 --> 00:04:04.820 align:middle line:84%
everything is moving according
to some particular plan.

00:04:04.820 --> 00:04:05.780 align:middle line:90%
>>BRADEN: Yeah.

00:04:05.780 --> 00:04:07.640 align:middle line:10%
>>LIPTON: An example
of that in real life

00:04:07.640 --> 00:04:10.320 align:middle line:10%
is when a butterfly,
a caterpillar,

00:04:10.320 --> 00:04:12.470 align:middle line:10%
has finished its maturation.

00:04:12.470 --> 00:04:14.930 align:middle line:84%
It creates a cocoon, and
it comes in one structure

00:04:14.930 --> 00:04:16.160 align:middle line:90%
as a caterpillar.

00:04:16.160 --> 00:04:18.777 align:middle line:84%
But it's going to move into
a structure of a butterfly.

00:04:18.777 --> 00:04:21.110 align:middle line:84%
Well, the same cells are going
to be in the caterpillar,

00:04:21.110 --> 00:04:23.210 align:middle line:84%
and they're also going to
contribute to the butterfly.

00:04:23.210 --> 00:04:24.120 align:middle line:90%
So how does it work?

00:04:24.120 --> 00:04:26.600 align:middle line:84%
And the answer
is, in the cocoon,

00:04:26.600 --> 00:04:30.230 align:middle line:84%
there's a breakdown of the
body of the caterpillar, where

00:04:30.230 --> 00:04:32.360 align:middle line:84%
the cells turn into like
a mush at some point.

00:04:32.360 --> 00:04:33.860 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: Would you
call that chaos?

00:04:33.860 --> 00:04:34.760 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: Well,
it's totally chaos.

00:04:34.760 --> 00:04:35.720 align:middle line:84%
Because if you look
at it, you say,

00:04:35.720 --> 00:04:37.430 align:middle line:84%
oh, the whole thing's
falling apart.

00:04:37.430 --> 00:04:40.130 align:middle line:84%
But on the other hand, as it's
falling apart, many of them

00:04:40.130 --> 00:04:42.470 align:middle line:84%
are also beginning to assemble
into the next structure

00:04:42.470 --> 00:04:43.680 align:middle line:90%
of the butterfly.

00:04:43.680 --> 00:04:45.537 align:middle line:84%
And so the point
is, on the surface,

00:04:45.537 --> 00:04:47.120 align:middle line:84%
it looks like it's
just falling apart.

00:04:47.120 --> 00:04:48.530 align:middle line:84%
But if you really
understood it, you

00:04:48.530 --> 00:04:50.120 align:middle line:84%
knew that these
cells from over here

00:04:50.120 --> 00:04:51.980 align:middle line:84%
are going to lose
this organization,

00:04:51.980 --> 00:04:54.870 align:middle line:84%
move, and then come into
this organization over here.

00:04:54.870 --> 00:04:58.730 align:middle line:84%
So between organization A
and B, the movement part

00:04:58.730 --> 00:05:01.760 align:middle line:84%
looks chaotic, looks
random, but it's chaotic.

00:05:01.760 --> 00:05:04.880 align:middle line:84%
Because all the cells know where
they're ultimately going to go.

00:05:04.880 --> 00:05:06.740 align:middle line:84%
And this is important
for us to understand

00:05:06.740 --> 00:05:09.080 align:middle line:84%
in our own particular
world for a simple reason.

00:05:09.080 --> 00:05:11.910 align:middle line:84%
We are facing what is called
the sixth mass extinction.

00:05:11.910 --> 00:05:14.030 align:middle line:84%
And it's due to human
behavior, the way we treat

00:05:14.030 --> 00:05:16.280 align:middle line:90%
Mother Nature and the planet.

00:05:16.280 --> 00:05:19.580 align:middle line:84%
And basically, the quote that
I used in a lecture and we used

00:05:19.580 --> 00:05:22.400 align:middle line:84%
it before it was "you cannot
solve the problems with

00:05:22.400 --> 00:05:24.830 align:middle line:84%
the same thinking that
created the problems."

00:05:24.830 --> 00:05:27.350 align:middle line:84%
And basically it says that
the civilization we're in

00:05:27.350 --> 00:05:31.550 align:middle line:84%
is the one whose culture
and behavior has caused

00:05:31.550 --> 00:05:33.330 align:middle line:90%
the sixth mass extinction.

00:05:33.330 --> 00:05:35.540 align:middle line:84%
So we have to take this
structure, the existing

00:05:35.540 --> 00:05:39.390 align:middle line:84%
structure, and transform
it into a more thrivable

00:05:39.390 --> 00:05:40.680 align:middle line:90%
whole structure.

00:05:40.680 --> 00:05:42.600 align:middle line:84%
And just like in
cymatics or just

00:05:42.600 --> 00:05:45.390 align:middle line:84%
like in the butterfly
and the caterpillar,

00:05:45.390 --> 00:05:49.345 align:middle line:84%
the old structure must fall
down so to build a new one.

00:05:49.345 --> 00:05:50.220 align:middle line:90%
>>BRADEN: Absolutely.

00:05:50.220 --> 00:05:52.803 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: But if you're in the
middle of this, all you can see

00:05:52.803 --> 00:05:54.720 align:middle line:84%
is, oh, my god, this
thing is falling down.

00:05:54.720 --> 00:05:56.700 align:middle line:90%
I'm scared.

00:05:56.700 --> 00:05:59.575 align:middle line:84%
And the reality about
it is that, yeah, it

00:05:59.575 --> 00:06:01.200 align:middle line:84%
provokes a lot of
fear in people to see

00:06:01.200 --> 00:06:03.093 align:middle line:90%
the world go in this upheaval.

00:06:03.093 --> 00:06:05.760 align:middle line:84%
But if you understand this, this
upheaval is not a random event.

00:06:05.760 --> 00:06:08.160 align:middle line:84%
It's a required event to
build another civilization,

00:06:08.160 --> 00:06:10.680 align:middle line:84%
but not on the existing
foundation of the one

00:06:10.680 --> 00:06:12.960 align:middle line:84%
we have, because that's
where the problems come from.

00:06:12.960 --> 00:06:14.835 align:middle line:84%
So when you look out at
the world and you go,

00:06:14.835 --> 00:06:16.950 align:middle line:84%
chaos, and a lot of people
are like, oh my god,

00:06:16.950 --> 00:06:21.480 align:middle line:84%
the world I know
is disappearing,

00:06:21.480 --> 00:06:23.270 align:middle line:84%
I have to say this
very seriously.

00:06:23.270 --> 00:06:25.770 align:middle line:84%
Thank god, because if you look
out the window and everything

00:06:25.770 --> 00:06:27.630 align:middle line:84%
stayed the same,
that says, man, we're

00:06:27.630 --> 00:06:30.010 align:middle line:84%
going to go into that
extinction even faster.

00:06:30.010 --> 00:06:32.550 align:middle line:84%
So chaos is a very
positive sign,

00:06:32.550 --> 00:06:35.850 align:middle line:84%
because it says we are moving
out of an existing system that

00:06:35.850 --> 00:06:39.000 align:middle line:84%
is causing a problem, and
in the process creating

00:06:39.000 --> 00:06:41.895 align:middle line:84%
a new system that will allow
us to thrive into the future.

00:06:41.895 --> 00:06:42.770 align:middle line:90%
>>BRADEN: Absolutely.

00:06:42.770 --> 00:06:44.187 align:middle line:84%
You know, one of
the things I see,

00:06:44.187 --> 00:06:47.160 align:middle line:84%
we have the benefit of
standing on a stage looking

00:06:47.160 --> 00:06:50.040 align:middle line:84%
at the faces of hundreds,
sometimes thousands of people

00:06:50.040 --> 00:06:53.990 align:middle line:84%
as we see them subconsciously
respond to what

00:06:53.990 --> 00:06:54.990 align:middle line:90%
it is that we're saying.

00:06:54.990 --> 00:06:58.170 align:middle line:84%
And one of the things that
I've found so fascinating,

00:06:58.170 --> 00:07:00.606 align:middle line:84%
no matter what the
culture or the language,

00:07:00.606 --> 00:07:03.660 align:middle line:84%
is that when people begin
to see the only things that

00:07:03.660 --> 00:07:07.110 align:middle line:84%
are in chaos right now, the only
systems that are breaking down,

00:07:07.110 --> 00:07:08.863 align:middle line:84%
are the systems that
are unsustainable.

00:07:08.863 --> 00:07:10.530 align:middle line:84%
There are a lot of
good things happening

00:07:10.530 --> 00:07:11.590 align:middle line:90%
that are very sustainable.

00:07:11.590 --> 00:07:13.200 align:middle line:84%
We're not hearing about them,
because they're not a problem.

00:07:13.200 --> 00:07:13.710 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: Right.

00:07:13.710 --> 00:07:16.380 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: But the unsustainable
systems are breaking down.

00:07:16.380 --> 00:07:18.290 align:middle line:84%
When we go back
to that cymatics,

00:07:18.290 --> 00:07:20.310 align:middle line:84%
I did an experiment
a few years ago,

00:07:20.310 --> 00:07:24.210 align:middle line:84%
and I tried it with an audience
that was a non-English speaking

00:07:24.210 --> 00:07:25.620 align:middle line:90%
audience.

00:07:25.620 --> 00:07:27.520 align:middle line:84%
Because I felt that
if it worked there,

00:07:27.520 --> 00:07:29.070 align:middle line:84%
it would probably
work everywhere.

00:07:29.070 --> 00:07:32.310 align:middle line:84%
And what I did was, I took
one of the cymatics images.

00:07:32.310 --> 00:07:34.650 align:middle line:84%
But rather than looking
at the entire image,

00:07:34.650 --> 00:07:38.110 align:middle line:84%
I zeroed in on a
portion of the image.

00:07:38.110 --> 00:07:40.050 align:middle line:84%
And when we looked
only at that piece,

00:07:40.050 --> 00:07:43.050 align:middle line:84%
it looked like the thing
was just in total chaos,

00:07:43.050 --> 00:07:45.120 align:middle line:90%
just totally falling apart.

00:07:45.120 --> 00:07:47.650 align:middle line:90%
No order whatsoever.

00:07:47.650 --> 00:07:51.150 align:middle line:84%
And when we stepped back to
a greater perspective, looked

00:07:51.150 --> 00:07:53.610 align:middle line:84%
at the big picture, we
could see that the change

00:07:53.610 --> 00:07:56.957 align:middle line:84%
we'd been looking at was
actually part of a pattern.

00:07:56.957 --> 00:07:59.040 align:middle line:84%
And it was a pattern that
was unfolding on a level

00:07:59.040 --> 00:08:03.480 align:middle line:84%
that we simply could not see
from our perspective of where

00:08:03.480 --> 00:08:05.388 align:middle line:90%
we were in that cymatics image.

00:08:05.388 --> 00:08:07.680 align:middle line:84%
And I think that is a very
powerful metaphor for what's

00:08:07.680 --> 00:08:10.850 align:middle line:90%
happening in the world today.

00:08:10.850 --> 00:08:15.510 align:middle line:84%
And it's easy to be
inundated with media 24/7,

00:08:15.510 --> 00:08:18.360 align:middle line:84%
with very biased
perspectives inundating

00:08:18.360 --> 00:08:22.020 align:middle line:84%
us to see these very specific
ways of looking at the world.

00:08:22.020 --> 00:08:24.280 align:middle line:84%
But if we can take a
breath, take a deep breath,

00:08:24.280 --> 00:08:27.240 align:middle line:84%
step back, look at
the big picture,

00:08:27.240 --> 00:08:28.740 align:middle line:84%
I think what we're
going to find is,

00:08:28.740 --> 00:08:32.490 align:middle line:84%
we are living this pivotal,
rare, precious moment

00:08:32.490 --> 00:08:36.880 align:middle line:84%
in the history of civilization
and of human evolution--

00:08:36.880 --> 00:08:38.580 align:middle line:90%
the evolution of consciousness.

00:08:38.580 --> 00:08:41.700 align:middle line:84%
Because we're being asked to
think and live differently,

00:08:41.700 --> 00:08:45.390 align:middle line:84%
more so now than perhaps we ever
have in our lifetimes for sure,

00:08:45.390 --> 00:08:47.530 align:middle line:84%
so that we can
accommodate that change.

00:08:47.530 --> 00:08:49.650 align:middle line:84%
And the important
thing about the chaos

00:08:49.650 --> 00:08:51.900 align:middle line:84%
is, when the system
breaks down the chaos,

00:08:51.900 --> 00:08:54.560 align:middle line:84%
it doesn't always go
back to square one.

00:08:54.560 --> 00:08:56.190 align:middle line:84%
Like, you have to
start all over.

00:08:56.190 --> 00:09:01.140 align:middle line:84%
The chaos gives way to a more
complex system, a higher order,

00:09:01.140 --> 00:09:04.313 align:middle line:84%
a more beautiful pattern if
you're looking at the cymatics.

00:09:04.313 --> 00:09:05.730 align:middle line:84%
And I think it's
important to have

00:09:05.730 --> 00:09:07.535 align:middle line:84%
that visual anchor
for people when

00:09:07.535 --> 00:09:08.910 align:middle line:84%
they think about
what's happening

00:09:08.910 --> 00:09:10.747 align:middle line:84%
in their own lives
in their world today.

00:09:10.747 --> 00:09:12.330 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: Well, I
also agree with you,

00:09:12.330 --> 00:09:14.220 align:middle line:84%
because as I said, if you
just look out the window

00:09:14.220 --> 00:09:16.410 align:middle line:84%
and you look at what's going
on, it could scare the heck out

00:09:16.410 --> 00:09:17.330 align:middle line:90%
of you.

