new and very different.

00:17:05.160 --> 00:17:06.260 align:middle line:90%
It tells us that.

00:17:06.260 --> 00:17:09.119 align:middle line:84%
And also "Avatar" was
so powerful with this.

00:17:09.119 --> 00:17:11.099 align:middle line:84%
It tells us about
the deep connection

00:17:11.099 --> 00:17:15.020 align:middle line:84%
that we have to all life,
to the Earth, to the planet.

00:17:15.020 --> 00:17:17.940 align:middle line:84%
And now the new discoveries
of plants themselves

00:17:17.940 --> 00:17:19.980 align:middle line:84%
are mirroring precisely
the principles

00:17:19.980 --> 00:17:21.347 align:middle line:90%
that "Avatar" shared with us.

00:17:21.347 --> 00:17:22.680 align:middle line:90%
Have you found those to be true?

00:17:22.680 --> 00:17:23.339 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: Absolutely true.

00:17:23.339 --> 00:17:25.960 align:middle line:84%
What's interesting is that when
we look at plants and we say,

00:17:25.960 --> 00:17:27.502 align:middle line:84%
oh, there's a tree
and there's a tree

00:17:27.502 --> 00:17:29.420 align:middle line:84%
and we separate them as
individual trees, what

00:17:29.420 --> 00:17:31.440 align:middle line:84%
we haven't seen is,
underneath the ground

00:17:31.440 --> 00:17:34.410 align:middle line:84%
all these trees are connected,
even different species.

00:17:34.410 --> 00:17:35.910 align:middle line:90%
They're all connected.

00:17:35.910 --> 00:17:40.380 align:middle line:84%
And mushrooms, fungus,
create pipelines

00:17:40.380 --> 00:17:42.840 align:middle line:90%
that connect the plants.

00:17:42.840 --> 00:17:45.690 align:middle line:84%
So when you look in a forest,
it looks like a whole bunch

00:17:45.690 --> 00:17:46.590 align:middle line:90%
of individual trees.

00:17:46.590 --> 00:17:48.300 align:middle line:84%
But if you could look
under the ground,

00:17:48.300 --> 00:17:50.080 align:middle line:84%
they're all connected
to each other.

00:17:50.080 --> 00:17:51.900 align:middle line:90%
It's a giant single organism.

00:17:51.900 --> 00:17:54.490 align:middle line:84%
And we are part of
that matrix as well.

00:17:54.490 --> 00:17:57.260 align:middle line:84%
And it's really information,
because plants, we always

00:17:57.260 --> 00:17:59.010 align:middle line:84%
look at them, oh,
animals are intelligent.

00:17:59.010 --> 00:18:00.843 align:middle line:84%
Plants are just those
things that sit there.

00:18:00.843 --> 00:18:03.180 align:middle line:84%
And I go, no, they
are so intelligent.

00:18:03.180 --> 00:18:05.140 align:middle line:84%
They communicate with
each other all the time.

00:18:05.140 --> 00:18:08.860 align:middle line:84%
And so if a disease is coming
from one side of the forest,

00:18:08.860 --> 00:18:11.070 align:middle line:84%
the first trees that
get that disease

00:18:11.070 --> 00:18:14.730 align:middle line:84%
send down information
already via the networks

00:18:14.730 --> 00:18:18.300 align:middle line:84%
of the mycelium, of the
fungus, or through pheromones,

00:18:18.300 --> 00:18:20.910 align:middle line:84%
soluble hormones that
go through the air.

00:18:20.910 --> 00:18:25.530 align:middle line:84%
And they can inform the forest
about a problem that's coming.

00:18:25.530 --> 00:18:28.170 align:middle line:84%
And the other plants
in that forest

00:18:28.170 --> 00:18:31.830 align:middle line:84%
will start to create behaviors
that will protect them

00:18:31.830 --> 00:18:33.040 align:middle line:90%
from this thing.

00:18:33.040 --> 00:18:35.910 align:middle line:84%
So the idea is that they're
always communicating.

00:18:35.910 --> 00:18:38.820 align:middle line:84%
And one interesting one is,
plants communicate with people,

00:18:38.820 --> 00:18:40.840 align:middle line:84%
but people don't
recognize it yet.

00:18:40.840 --> 00:18:44.610 align:middle line:84%
And they found out that
a person who grows plants

00:18:44.610 --> 00:18:48.930 align:middle line:84%
in their house, let's say, the
plants identify the vibration,

00:18:48.930 --> 00:18:50.550 align:middle line:90%
the energy of that person.

00:18:50.550 --> 00:18:52.500 align:middle line:84%
When that person
shows up in the room,

00:18:52.500 --> 00:18:56.100 align:middle line:84%
the plants release pheromones,
soluble hormones, in the air.

00:18:56.100 --> 00:18:57.100 align:middle line:90%
To do what?

00:18:57.100 --> 00:18:59.430 align:middle line:84%
Bring that entity
over, because that's

00:18:59.430 --> 00:19:02.550 align:middle line:84%
the entity that services them,
gives them water and nutrition

00:19:02.550 --> 00:19:03.490 align:middle line:90%
and all that.

00:19:03.490 --> 00:19:05.460 align:middle line:84%
So when that energy
walks into the room,

00:19:05.460 --> 00:19:08.880 align:middle line:84%
the plants know that energy,
release the pheromones

00:19:08.880 --> 00:19:10.922 align:middle line:84%
with the intention of
"come and take care of me."

00:19:10.922 --> 00:19:13.088 align:middle line:84%
And it's interesting, because
if somebody else walks

00:19:13.088 --> 00:19:15.390 align:middle line:84%
in the room, plants will
not release the pheromones.

00:19:15.390 --> 00:19:16.190 align:middle line:90%
>>BRADEN: Exactly.

00:19:16.190 --> 00:19:17.850 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: So this
is intelligence way

00:19:17.850 --> 00:19:19.200 align:middle line:84%
beyond anything
we've ever conceived.

00:19:19.200 --> 00:19:20.000 align:middle line:90%
>>BRADEN: There is.

00:19:20.000 --> 00:19:22.170 align:middle line:10%
One of the places
where I saw that taken

00:19:22.170 --> 00:19:24.970 align:middle line:10%
to even another level,
and you may have visited,

00:19:24.970 --> 00:19:28.830 align:middle line:10%
Damanhur in Italy, the
intentional community.

00:19:28.830 --> 00:19:32.490 align:middle line:84%
They live close to the
earth, very earth-based,

00:19:32.490 --> 00:19:35.710 align:middle line:84%
really supporting this
primal relationship

00:19:35.710 --> 00:19:37.710 align:middle line:84%
that we have with the
earth and with all plants.

00:19:37.710 --> 00:19:39.990 align:middle line:84%
And the first visit that I had,
they invited me to come over,

00:19:39.990 --> 00:19:42.323 align:middle line:84%
and they wanted to share with
me some of the technology.

00:19:42.323 --> 00:19:48.030 align:middle line:84%
And they are developing some
pretty outrageous technology

00:19:48.030 --> 00:19:50.070 align:middle line:84%
compared to the way
we've been taught

00:19:50.070 --> 00:19:52.860 align:middle line:84%
to think about the world,
but it makes total sense

00:19:52.860 --> 00:19:54.810 align:middle line:84%
when we think about
this interconnection

00:19:54.810 --> 00:19:56.130 align:middle line:90%
that you're talking about.

00:19:56.130 --> 00:19:57.505 align:middle line:84%
One of of the
things I saw when I

00:19:57.505 --> 00:19:59.460 align:middle line:90%
went there was, I walked into--

00:19:59.460 --> 00:20:01.470 align:middle line:90%
it was in a tent, actually.

00:20:01.470 --> 00:20:03.240 align:middle line:84%
And they had a number
of different plants,

00:20:03.240 --> 00:20:06.210 align:middle line:84%
and they had machines
wired up to the plants.

00:20:06.210 --> 00:20:09.090 align:middle line:84%
And I'm a musician when I'm
not doing what I'm doing now.

00:20:09.090 --> 00:20:11.790 align:middle line:84%
And I always notice
audio equipment.

00:20:11.790 --> 00:20:14.070 align:middle line:84%
And the first thing I
saw, there were speakers.

00:20:14.070 --> 00:20:17.220 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, they're either
playing music to the plants,

00:20:17.220 --> 00:20:20.247 align:middle line:84%
or the plants are
saying something to us.

00:20:20.247 --> 00:20:21.330 align:middle line:90%
Because I was at Damanhur.

00:20:21.330 --> 00:20:24.090 align:middle line:84%
And so I said, can you tell
me what's happening here?

00:20:24.090 --> 00:20:28.200 align:middle line:84%
They had electrodes hooked
up to different portions

00:20:28.200 --> 00:20:29.460 align:middle line:90%
of the plants.

00:20:29.460 --> 00:20:31.350 align:middle line:84%
And what they found
was, when they

00:20:31.350 --> 00:20:34.800 align:middle line:84%
would touch the plants in very
specific ways, same thing.

00:20:34.800 --> 00:20:38.500 align:middle line:84%
The plants would emit
a frequency, inaudible.

00:20:38.500 --> 00:20:41.500 align:middle line:84%
And the devices
capture that frequency

00:20:41.500 --> 00:20:44.893 align:middle line:84%
and bumped it up to a level
that the human ear could hear.

00:20:44.893 --> 00:20:47.560 align:middle line:84%
And it literally-- Bruce, I have
to tell you, it was a symphony.

00:20:47.560 --> 00:20:50.690 align:middle line:84%
It was so beautiful, we
didn't want to leave.

00:20:50.690 --> 00:20:52.750 align:middle line:84%
And there were
multiple plants who

00:20:52.750 --> 00:20:54.665 align:middle line:84%
were emitting these
beautiful-- it

00:20:54.665 --> 00:20:57.350 align:middle line:90%
was symphony at the same time.

00:20:57.350 --> 00:20:59.720 align:middle line:84%
And when you begin to think
about plants in that way,

00:20:59.720 --> 00:21:02.530 align:middle line:84%
and if you do an experiment, if
you take a leaf off of a plant,

00:21:02.530 --> 00:21:04.973 align:middle line:84%
they let you know that that's
a trauma for them, because--

00:21:04.973 --> 00:21:06.640 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: Don't say
that to vegetarians.

00:21:06.640 --> 00:21:09.640 align:middle line:84%
They're going to be very
upset about eating plants.

00:21:09.640 --> 00:21:11.350 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: Because the
frequency changes.

00:21:11.350 --> 00:21:15.150 align:middle line:84%
All of this, these are all
discoveries in different ways

00:21:15.150 --> 00:21:17.470 align:middle line:84%
that go to this very
fundamental idea

00:21:17.470 --> 00:21:19.805 align:middle line:84%
that we are so deeply
connected to this world.

00:21:19.805 --> 00:21:21.430 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: They found
out the same thing

00:21:21.430 --> 00:21:25.330 align:middle line:84%
with the crickets in the
field make vibrational sounds,

00:21:25.330 --> 00:21:26.680 align:middle line:90%
with the cricket sounds.

00:21:26.680 --> 00:21:29.890 align:middle line:84%
And then what they found is that
when the crickets disappeared,

00:21:29.890 --> 00:21:31.480 align:middle line:90%
the plants didn't do very well.

00:21:31.480 --> 00:21:34.193 align:middle line:84%
So the experiment was in
a field with no crickets,

00:21:34.193 --> 00:21:35.860 align:middle line:84%
and then a field where
they put speakers

00:21:35.860 --> 00:21:37.660 align:middle line:90%
in and played the crickets.

00:21:37.660 --> 00:21:40.022 align:middle line:84%
And the difference in
growth was profound.

00:21:40.022 --> 00:21:41.980 align:middle line:84%
The ones with the crickets,
the plants grew up.

00:21:41.980 --> 00:21:45.573 align:middle line:84%
There's a harmony in the
world, and quantum physics

00:21:45.573 --> 00:21:46.990 align:middle line:84%
is the thing that
says all of this

00:21:46.990 --> 00:21:48.670 align:middle line:84%
is connected, because
it says it's not

00:21:48.670 --> 00:21:51.550 align:middle line:84%
the physical expression that's
important in quantum physics.

00:21:51.550 --> 00:21:52.810 align:middle line:90%
It's the energy.

00:21:52.810 --> 00:21:55.660 align:middle line:84%
And that all energy, you
can't separate energy.

00:21:55.660 --> 00:21:57.100 align:middle line:90%
I can separate physical things.

00:21:57.100 --> 00:21:59.017 align:middle line:84%
I could take these two
hands and separate them

00:21:59.017 --> 00:22:01.720 align:middle line:84%
into two different hands,
but the energy of the hands

00:22:01.720 --> 00:22:03.430 align:middle line:90%
can never be separated.

00:22:03.430 --> 00:22:05.410 align:middle line:90%
Energy is in the field.

00:22:05.410 --> 00:22:07.240 align:middle line:84%
It's ripples, and
they all connect.

00:22:07.240 --> 00:22:10.390 align:middle line:84%
And this is why quantum
physics talks about unity

00:22:10.390 --> 00:22:11.680 align:middle line:90%
of the entire planet.

00:22:11.680 --> 00:22:13.957 align:middle line:84%
Everything is connected
to everything,

00:22:13.957 --> 00:22:15.790 align:middle line:84%
because everything is
energy, and everything

00:22:15.790 --> 00:22:17.630 align:middle line:90%
is vibration and waves.

00:22:17.630 --> 00:22:21.855 align:middle line:84%
And this is what we have lost
when we believe in a Newtonian

00:22:21.855 --> 00:22:24.230 align:middle line:84%
world, that I'm separate from
you, and you're over there,

00:22:24.230 --> 00:22:25.230 align:middle line:90%
and we're not connected.

00:22:25.230 --> 00:22:26.770 align:middle line:84%
And it's like, in
a quantum physics

00:22:26.770 --> 00:22:28.295 align:middle line:90%
world, that's completely wrong.

00:22:28.295 --> 00:22:29.170 align:middle line:90%
>>BRADEN: Absolutely.

00:22:29.170 --> 00:22:31.510 align:middle line:84%
And I think this is one
of the themes, again, that

00:22:31.510 --> 00:22:35.040 align:middle line:84%
is being reflected back through
these very powerful films.

00:22:35.040 --> 00:22:36.660 align:middle line:90%
I mean, I see these films.

00:22:36.660 --> 00:22:38.650 align:middle line:84%
Where did "The Matrix"
even come from?

00:22:38.650 --> 00:22:40.585 align:middle line:84%
I mean, the idea for
"The Matrix," yeah,

00:22:40.585 --> 00:22:42.730 align:middle line:84%
it came from the brothers
that developed it,

00:22:42.730 --> 00:22:46.090 align:middle line:84%
but where in the field did their
consciousness even pick this

00:22:46.090 --> 00:22:46.890 align:middle line:90%
up?

00:22:46.890 --> 00:22:48.580 align:middle line:90%
It was consciousness.

00:22:48.580 --> 00:22:52.180 align:middle line:84%
Were we calling forth,
asking for that film

00:22:52.180 --> 00:22:54.650 align:middle line:84%
to be made to remind us of
something about ourselves?

00:22:54.650 --> 00:22:56.483 align:middle line:84%
And one of the themes
is precisely what

00:22:56.483 --> 00:22:57.400 align:middle line:90%
we were talking about.

00:22:57.400 --> 00:23:00.800 align:middle line:84%
Because in addition to
"Avatar," for example,

00:23:00.800 --> 00:23:04.780 align:middle line:84%
being a very earth-based
and very much

00:23:04.780 --> 00:23:09.580 align:middle line:84%
about the connectivity of all
life, the theme of conflict

00:23:09.580 --> 00:23:11.490 align:middle line:84%
comes up in every
one of these films.

00:23:11.490 --> 00:23:14.410 align:middle line:84%
Somewhere there is
some kind of conflict.

00:23:14.410 --> 00:23:20.260 align:middle line:84%
And the key in each of the
films is that within each of us

00:23:20.260 --> 00:23:24.650 align:middle line:84%
we have this untapped
potential not just to survive,

00:23:24.650 --> 00:23:29.260 align:middle line:84%
but to transcend, to become
more than what that conflict has

00:23:29.260 --> 00:23:30.985 align:middle line:90%
led us to embrace in the past.

00:23:30.985 --> 00:23:32.360 align:middle line:84%
And when I think
of that, I mean,

00:23:32.360 --> 00:23:34.460 align:middle line:84%
it almost brings
tears to my eyes,

00:23:34.460 --> 00:23:36.760 align:middle line:84%
because that's where
we are right now.

00:23:36.760 --> 00:23:40.540 align:middle line:84%
The idea of war as we've
known it in the past I believe

00:23:40.540 --> 00:23:42.430 align:middle line:90%
has become obsolete.

00:23:42.430 --> 00:23:46.060 align:middle line:84%
In the old 20th
century, the idea of war

00:23:46.060 --> 00:23:48.550 align:middle line:84%
was that there were
winners and losers,

00:23:48.550 --> 00:23:51.580 align:middle line:84%
and that there was something to
be gained from this conflict.

00:23:51.580 --> 00:23:54.220 align:middle line:84%
And now we know, with the
technology that we have,

00:23:54.220 --> 00:23:56.890 align:middle line:84%
the weapons we have
today, the chemicals

00:23:56.890 --> 00:23:59.320 align:middle line:84%
we have today, war,
everybody loses.

00:23:59.320 --> 00:24:00.660 align:middle line:90%
There's nothing to be gained.

00:24:00.660 --> 00:24:03.490 align:middle line:10%
So I believe, and I want to
see where you are on this,

00:24:03.490 --> 00:24:06.460 align:middle line:10%
I believe that we are
the generation that

00:24:06.460 --> 00:24:12.100 align:middle line:10%
is coming to the understanding
where war is becoming obsolete.

00:24:12.100 --> 00:24:16.050 align:middle line:84%
War as we've known it in the
past has become obsolete.

00:24:16.050 --> 00:24:19.360 align:middle line:84%
And that by embracing
this inner potential

00:24:19.360 --> 00:24:22.578 align:middle line:84%
to transcend the conflict,
that is the evolutionary leap

00:24:22.578 --> 00:24:23.870 align:middle line:90%
that's going to take us beyond.

00:24:23.870 --> 00:24:25.985 align:middle line:84%
And that's what all
those films are showing.

00:24:25.985 --> 00:24:27.610 align:middle line:84%
That's what all the
movies are showing.

00:24:27.610 --> 00:24:28.720 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: Absolutely.

00:24:28.720 --> 00:24:31.790 align:middle line:84%
And where do people
get these ideas?

00:24:31.790 --> 00:24:32.590 align:middle line:90%
It's intuition.

00:24:32.590 --> 00:24:34.190 align:middle line:90%
It comes from out of the body.

00:24:34.190 --> 00:24:34.990 align:middle line:90%
It's downloaded.

00:24:34.990 --> 00:24:37.690 align:middle line:84%
It's interesting, because
scientists and artists

00:24:37.690 --> 00:24:40.000 align:middle line:84%
do their work in another
realm, and then bring it back

00:24:40.000 --> 00:24:41.360 align:middle line:90%
into this realm.

00:24:41.360 --> 00:24:43.345 align:middle line:84%
And so there are truths
that are fundamental.

00:24:43.345 --> 00:24:45.220 align:middle line:84%
And if you go out there
and you pull them in,

00:24:45.220 --> 00:24:47.410 align:middle line:84%
that's why there are no
new stories, so to speak,

00:24:47.410 --> 00:24:49.788 align:middle line:84%
because they all are based
on the same kind of truth.

00:24:49.788 --> 00:24:51.830 align:middle line:84%
Just how you tell it might
be a little different,

00:24:51.830 --> 00:24:53.290 align:middle line:90%
but they're all the same story.

00:24:53.290 --> 00:24:53.390 align:middle line:90%
>>BRADEN: Yeah.

00:24:53.390 --> 00:24:55.098 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: And we're
facing that, and it's

00:24:55.098 --> 00:24:59.110 align:middle line:84%
important to recognize that,
yes, the idea of conflict,

00:24:59.110 --> 00:25:03.160 align:middle line:84%
an old belief system supported
by a Darwinian theory that

00:25:03.160 --> 00:25:05.770 align:middle line:84%
says, that's the
only way out, is

00:25:05.770 --> 00:25:07.510 align:middle line:84%
a failure, because
Darwinian theory is

00:25:07.510 --> 00:25:09.580 align:middle line:84%
a failure in that
regard, that we're

00:25:09.580 --> 00:25:11.290 align:middle line:84%
coming together
in a new community

00:25:11.290 --> 00:25:12.370 align:middle line:90%
and new understanding.

00:25:12.370 --> 00:25:15.340 align:middle line:84%
The internet is
actually the creation

00:25:15.340 --> 00:25:17.230 align:middle line:84%
of a global nervous
system that can

00:25:17.230 --> 00:25:20.950 align:middle line:84%
hook eight billion human
cells together into one body.

00:25:20.950 --> 00:25:22.690 align:middle line:84%
Once that internet
was created, it

00:25:22.690 --> 00:25:26.100 align:middle line:84%
changed everybody's perspective,
because you don't see borders

00:25:26.100 --> 00:25:27.790 align:middle line:90%
in the internet.

00:25:27.790 --> 00:25:30.160 align:middle line:84%
And those people,
the Arab Spring

00:25:30.160 --> 00:25:31.990 align:middle line:84%
resulted because they
were looking at--

00:25:31.990 --> 00:25:32.110 align:middle line:90%
>>BRADEN: Twitter.

00:25:32.110 --> 00:25:33.860 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: --What was
going on in the West,

00:25:33.860 --> 00:25:36.190 align:middle line:84%
and looking at their own
place going, why is this?

00:25:36.190 --> 00:25:38.650 align:middle line:84%
Once we all got
connected-- and I

00:25:38.650 --> 00:25:42.220 align:middle line:84%
would like to add a part about
the younger generation, which

00:25:42.220 --> 00:25:45.458 align:middle line:84%
I would collectively say,
from millennials on down,

00:25:45.458 --> 00:25:47.500 align:middle line:84%
they've always looked at
life as, oh my god, it's

00:25:47.500 --> 00:25:48.300 align:middle line:90%
so much trouble.

00:25:48.300 --> 00:25:51.760 align:middle line:84%
We owe all this money, can't
pay off the education debt,

00:25:51.760 --> 00:25:54.430 align:middle line:84%
can't get a job, three or
four trying to live together

00:25:54.430 --> 00:25:57.140 align:middle line:84%
in the same apartment,
and there's this very doom

00:25:57.140 --> 00:25:58.880 align:middle line:90%
and gloom kind of thing.

00:25:58.880 --> 00:26:01.510 align:middle line:84%
And I just want to
acknowledge to them, no,

00:26:01.510 --> 00:26:03.280 align:middle line:84%
that they play the
most important part

00:26:03.280 --> 00:26:05.260 align:middle line:84%
in this evolution
for a simple reason--

00:26:05.260 --> 00:26:07.330 align:middle line:84%
not being connected
to the structure

00:26:07.330 --> 00:26:11.170 align:middle line:84%
allows them to generate a
structure different than.

00:26:11.170 --> 00:26:15.280 align:middle line:84%
And so really, the drive
force of this evolution

00:26:15.280 --> 00:26:18.560 align:middle line:84%
will be the younger
generation, because they

00:26:18.560 --> 00:26:21.100 align:middle line:84%
have been separated from the
structure in the first place.

00:26:21.100 --> 00:26:24.700 align:middle line:84%
And they're much more
than 50% of the population

00:26:24.700 --> 00:26:25.940 align:middle line:90%
around the world.

00:26:25.940 --> 00:26:28.122 align:middle line:84%
And they're all connected
via the internet.

00:26:28.122 --> 00:26:30.580 align:middle line:84%
So this is really, when you
look at it, it's like, oh yeah,

00:26:30.580 --> 00:26:32.830 align:middle line:84%
this is moving
into this direction

00:26:32.830 --> 00:26:34.420 align:middle line:90%
of a new civilization.

00:26:34.420 --> 00:26:37.720 align:middle line:84%
And thank god we're still
here, because elders,

00:26:37.720 --> 00:26:38.960 align:middle line:90%
we're not thrown out.

00:26:38.960 --> 00:26:41.720 align:middle line:84%
We have advice and things
that we have learned.

00:26:41.720 --> 00:26:46.150 align:middle line:84%
So thank you for
bringing in a science

00:26:46.150 --> 00:26:48.700 align:middle line:84%
that we can pass on
to the millennials,

00:26:48.700 --> 00:26:50.825 align:middle line:84%
that they can use to create
the world that we need.

00:26:50.825 --> 00:26:52.492 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: When did
we become the elders?

00:26:52.492 --> 00:26:53.450 align:middle line:90%
When did that happen?

00:26:53.450 --> 00:26:54.430 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:26:54.430 --> 00:26:56.250 align:middle line:84%
I remember the first
time, the first time

00:26:56.250 --> 00:26:58.000 align:middle line:84%
somebody in the audience
raised their hand

00:26:58.000 --> 00:26:59.420 align:middle line:90%
and said "Mr. Braden."

00:26:59.420 --> 00:27:00.650 align:middle line:90%
And I thought "Gregg?

00:27:00.650 --> 00:27:02.250 align:middle line:90%
You mean Gregg?"

00:27:02.250 --> 00:27:03.730 align:middle line:90%
It's really interesting.

00:27:03.730 --> 00:27:06.185 align:middle line:84%
we are considered elders
now, and I'm not sure

00:27:06.185 --> 00:27:07.310 align:middle line:90%
exactly when that happened.

00:27:07.310 --> 00:27:09.820 align:middle line:84%
But I want just about
a half a step back.

00:27:09.820 --> 00:27:12.160 align:middle line:84%
Something you said
was so important.

00:27:12.160 --> 00:27:14.820 align:middle line:84%
I had the privilege
a few years ago

00:27:14.820 --> 00:27:18.550 align:middle line:84%
of doing a number of
conferences with a man who

00:27:18.550 --> 00:27:21.740 align:middle line:84%
I have tremendous respect
for, I admire, Michio Kaku.

00:27:21.740 --> 00:27:22.540 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: Oh, yes.

