00:35:32.490 --> 00:35:34.920 align:middle line:84%
And to get out is to
listen to the science

00:35:34.920 --> 00:35:37.350 align:middle line:84%
that you talk about, the
science that I talk about

00:35:37.350 --> 00:35:40.500 align:middle line:84%
and say, it's our choice
to change consciousness.

00:35:40.500 --> 00:35:43.980 align:middle line:84%
Because that, even according
to quantum physics,

00:35:43.980 --> 00:35:45.550 align:middle line:84%
is what's creating
this whole thing.

00:35:45.550 --> 00:35:46.060 align:middle line:90%
>>BRADEN: Sure.

00:35:46.060 --> 00:35:47.393 align:middle line:90%
Well, it's a very different way.

00:35:47.393 --> 00:35:49.620 align:middle line:84%
What we're talking about,
it's based on science.

00:35:49.620 --> 00:35:52.560 align:middle line:84%
It's a very different
way for people to think.

00:35:52.560 --> 00:35:54.150 align:middle line:90%
I'm a systems thinker.

00:35:54.150 --> 00:35:58.668 align:middle line:84%
So I like to be in the
nanosecond of right now.

00:35:58.668 --> 00:36:00.460 align:middle line:84%
But I also like to look
at the big picture.

00:36:00.460 --> 00:36:02.377 align:middle line:84%
And these are the kinds
of discoveries, Bruce.

00:36:02.377 --> 00:36:05.280 align:middle line:84%
I cannot help but think
that these are the kinds

00:36:05.280 --> 00:36:10.420 align:middle line:84%
of discoveries that expand our
understanding of who we are

00:36:10.420 --> 00:36:13.330 align:middle line:84%
and how we relate to one
another that will break down

00:36:13.330 --> 00:36:17.320 align:middle line:84%
the barriers that have separated
us precisely at the time when

00:36:17.320 --> 00:36:19.600 align:middle line:90%
the world is being pushed.

00:36:19.600 --> 00:36:24.730 align:middle line:84%
We're being mushed together
as cultures, and religions,

00:36:24.730 --> 00:36:25.928 align:middle line:90%
and the ways that we think.

00:36:25.928 --> 00:36:27.970 align:middle line:84%
The way that men are taught
to think about women,

00:36:27.970 --> 00:36:29.140 align:middle line:90%
that women think about men.

00:36:29.140 --> 00:36:30.057 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: Programming.

00:36:30.057 --> 00:36:32.370 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: Yeah, all of
that, for the first time,

00:36:32.370 --> 00:36:35.870 align:middle line:84%
we are globalizing almost eight
billion people on the planet.

00:36:35.870 --> 00:36:37.900 align:middle line:84%
And we're trying to
accommodate the change

00:36:37.900 --> 00:36:40.720 align:middle line:84%
through a thinking based
in the false assumptions

00:36:40.720 --> 00:36:43.300 align:middle line:84%
of an obsolete science of
separation, competition,

00:36:43.300 --> 00:36:44.100 align:middle line:90%
conflict.

00:36:44.100 --> 00:36:45.350 align:middle line:90%
And it's not working.

00:36:45.350 --> 00:36:48.070 align:middle line:84%
So these are the discoveries
that give us the reason

00:36:48.070 --> 00:36:48.980 align:middle line:90%
to think differently.

00:36:48.980 --> 00:36:52.510 align:middle line:84%
And I think they are the
kinds of discoveries that--

00:36:52.510 --> 00:36:53.420 align:middle line:90%
two things.

00:36:53.420 --> 00:36:57.010 align:middle line:84%
They are going to
lead us to a deeper

00:36:57.010 --> 00:36:58.207 align:middle line:90%
understanding of ourselves.

00:36:58.207 --> 00:37:00.040 align:middle line:84%
The better we know
ourselves, the less we're

00:37:00.040 --> 00:37:01.623 align:middle line:84%
going to fear the
change in the world,

00:37:01.623 --> 00:37:05.560 align:middle line:84%
the less we fear other people
and ultimately our own power.

00:37:05.560 --> 00:37:06.730 align:middle line:90%
But the second thing--

00:37:06.730 --> 00:37:10.760 align:middle line:84%
and you and I have had
this conversation before--

00:37:10.760 --> 00:37:14.550 align:middle line:84%
in the 1990s, I met a
Native American man here.

00:37:14.550 --> 00:37:16.550 align:middle line:84%
We're in the high desert
of northern New Mexico,

00:37:16.550 --> 00:37:18.740 align:middle line:84%
and it wasn't far from
here where I met this man.

00:37:18.740 --> 00:37:21.460 align:middle line:84%
Never seen him
before in my life.

00:37:21.460 --> 00:37:23.220 align:middle line:84%
We were hiking through
the high desert

00:37:23.220 --> 00:37:26.490 align:middle line:84%
of an archaeological
site called Chaco Canyon.

00:37:26.490 --> 00:37:30.190 align:middle line:90%
And we just hit it off.

00:37:30.190 --> 00:37:32.590 align:middle line:90%
I was with my mom at the time.

00:37:32.590 --> 00:37:37.630 align:middle line:84%
And him seeing a grown man with
his mother in a sacred site

00:37:37.630 --> 00:37:40.930 align:middle line:84%
and the respect to an
elder was the doorway

00:37:40.930 --> 00:37:43.480 align:middle line:84%
that made him feel very
comfortable in communicating

00:37:43.480 --> 00:37:44.500 align:middle line:90%
with me.

00:37:44.500 --> 00:37:48.010 align:middle line:84%
And he told me a
story, and my mom.

00:37:48.010 --> 00:37:52.375 align:middle line:84%
And the story was essentially
that a long time ago, people

00:37:52.375 --> 00:37:54.250 align:middle line:84%
on the earth lived very
differently than they

00:37:54.250 --> 00:37:56.590 align:middle line:84%
do right now, and they were
deeply connected to themselves

00:37:56.590 --> 00:37:57.390 align:middle line:90%
and one another.

00:37:57.390 --> 00:37:58.530 align:middle line:90%
Something happened.

00:37:58.530 --> 00:37:59.890 align:middle line:90%
And they don't know what.

00:37:59.890 --> 00:38:01.420 align:middle line:90%
People got lost.

00:38:01.420 --> 00:38:03.015 align:middle line:84%
And they so longed
for the connection

00:38:03.015 --> 00:38:04.390 align:middle line:84%
that they used to
have-- and this

00:38:04.390 --> 00:38:05.770 align:middle line:90%
is where it gets interesting.

00:38:05.770 --> 00:38:08.410 align:middle line:84%
He said that people so
longed for that connection

00:38:08.410 --> 00:38:13.050 align:middle line:84%
they began to build in the
world outside of their bodies

00:38:13.050 --> 00:38:16.860 align:middle line:84%
the machines that mimic the
function that we already

00:38:16.860 --> 00:38:17.670 align:middle line:90%
have within.

00:38:17.670 --> 00:38:19.780 align:middle line:84%
And he said we live
in that world now.

00:38:19.780 --> 00:38:23.310 align:middle line:84%
And the world will become
more and more and more complex

00:38:23.310 --> 00:38:25.860 align:middle line:84%
until we recognize that
everything we built out there,

00:38:25.860 --> 00:38:29.760 align:middle line:84%
in one way or another, it mimics
what we already are in here.

00:38:29.760 --> 00:38:31.740 align:middle line:84%
And the day that
that happens, we

00:38:31.740 --> 00:38:34.350 align:middle line:84%
no longer need the complexity
of that outer world

00:38:34.350 --> 00:38:38.850 align:middle line:84%
because we are now
more sophisticated,

00:38:38.850 --> 00:38:42.390 align:middle line:84%
but simplified as we embrace
our own inner technology.

00:38:42.390 --> 00:38:43.780 align:middle line:90%
And I thought, wow.

00:38:43.780 --> 00:38:44.580 align:middle line:90%
What?

00:38:44.580 --> 00:38:46.950 align:middle line:84%
And that's what all
these stories are about.

00:38:46.950 --> 00:38:50.130 align:middle line:84%
"The Matrix," they're all
about human potential,

00:38:50.130 --> 00:38:53.790 align:middle line:84%
that we are wired to thrive
in these times of extremes.

00:38:53.790 --> 00:38:55.710 align:middle line:84%
And we have this
untapped potential,

00:38:55.710 --> 00:38:58.260 align:middle line:84%
because every cell
in our body does--

00:38:58.260 --> 00:38:59.720 align:middle line:90%
I work in a high tech industry.

00:38:59.720 --> 00:39:02.790 align:middle line:84%
I worked in Star Wars,
SDI, during the Cold War,

00:39:02.790 --> 00:39:06.070 align:middle line:84%
laser systems, complex
information systems.

00:39:06.070 --> 00:39:08.820 align:middle line:84%
I've never seen anything
built, Bruce, outside of us

00:39:08.820 --> 00:39:12.840 align:middle line:84%
that does not mimic what we
already are in ourselves.

00:39:12.840 --> 00:39:16.230 align:middle line:84%
And we've got 50 trillion
plus of these cells.

00:39:16.230 --> 00:39:19.380 align:middle line:84%
As we learn to
master and harmonize

00:39:19.380 --> 00:39:22.285 align:middle line:84%
this inner technology, we don't
need all this stuff out here.

00:39:22.285 --> 00:39:23.160 align:middle line:90%
>>LIPTON: Absolutely.

00:39:23.160 --> 00:39:25.620 align:middle line:84%
And in fact, the leading
edge of biological research

00:39:25.620 --> 00:39:26.940 align:middle line:90%
is called "biomimicry."

00:39:26.940 --> 00:39:28.680 align:middle line:84%
It says that if you
want to do it right,

00:39:28.680 --> 00:39:30.430 align:middle line:84%
then you have to see
how the body does it,

00:39:30.430 --> 00:39:33.990 align:middle line:84%
because it's had several billion
years of making it right.

00:39:33.990 --> 00:39:36.690 align:middle line:84%
And so the technologies
that are in the body

00:39:36.690 --> 00:39:39.650 align:middle line:84%
exceed the technologies
that humans create.

00:39:39.650 --> 00:39:40.920 align:middle line:90%
>>BRADEN: Absolutely.

00:39:40.920 --> 00:39:42.337 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: And as
a cell biologist,

00:39:42.337 --> 00:39:44.790 align:middle line:84%
I get a lot of joy out of it,
because people have always

00:39:44.790 --> 00:39:46.350 align:middle line:84%
believed, well,
humans are smart,

00:39:46.350 --> 00:39:49.000 align:middle line:84%
and every time you go down
to the next lower animal,

00:39:49.000 --> 00:39:50.880 align:middle line:84%
there's less intelligence,
less intelligence,

00:39:50.880 --> 00:39:52.420 align:middle line:84%
and then you get
down to the cell.

00:39:52.420 --> 00:39:54.795 align:middle line:84%
And you say, well, how much
intelligence can a cell have?

00:39:54.795 --> 00:39:57.660 align:middle line:84%
And then I turn around
and go, they created us.

00:39:57.660 --> 00:40:00.030 align:middle line:84%
They created us with
technology that we can't even

00:40:00.030 --> 00:40:01.650 align:middle line:90%
duplicate at this moment.

00:40:01.650 --> 00:40:05.350 align:middle line:84%
And this is why they're all
saying, the answers lie within.

00:40:05.350 --> 00:40:06.690 align:middle line:90%
And I totally believe it.

00:40:06.690 --> 00:40:09.270 align:middle line:84%
Inside here, 50
trillion cells learning

00:40:09.270 --> 00:40:12.600 align:middle line:84%
to live in harmony in a healthy
human body, there's a politics.

00:40:12.600 --> 00:40:13.670 align:middle line:90%
There's an economy.

00:40:13.670 --> 00:40:15.640 align:middle line:90%
There is a social structure.

00:40:15.640 --> 00:40:17.730 align:middle line:84%
And I said, what
we need to learn

00:40:17.730 --> 00:40:20.245 align:middle line:84%
is how do 50 trillion cells
live in harmony like that?

00:40:20.245 --> 00:40:21.120 align:middle line:90%
>>BRADEN: Absolutely.

00:40:21.120 --> 00:40:22.330 align:middle line:90%
I think this is the key.

00:40:22.330 --> 00:40:25.757 align:middle line:84%
And that's where I want to
close with this segment is,

00:40:25.757 --> 00:40:27.590 align:middle line:84%
people are asking-- all
this is interesting.

00:40:27.590 --> 00:40:29.130 align:middle line:84%
People in their
mind, I know they're

00:40:29.130 --> 00:40:30.250 align:middle line:90%
saying same thing I say.

00:40:30.250 --> 00:40:31.590 align:middle line:84%
What do we do with
all this information?

00:40:31.590 --> 00:40:33.660 align:middle line:84%
Where do we go with this,
and in a world that's

00:40:33.660 --> 00:40:36.240 align:middle line:84%
changing faster than we can
document in our textbooks

00:40:36.240 --> 00:40:37.480 align:middle line:90%
and teach in our classrooms?

00:40:37.480 --> 00:40:40.790 align:middle line:84%
And I think you have
nailed the answer--

00:40:40.790 --> 00:40:42.480 align:middle line:90%
nature is the model.

00:40:42.480 --> 00:40:45.520 align:middle line:84%
And that model is playing
out through the cells

00:40:45.520 --> 00:40:46.320 align:middle line:90%
in our bodies.

00:40:46.320 --> 00:40:49.890 align:middle line:84%
And if we ever
forget, or we doubt

00:40:49.890 --> 00:40:53.640 align:middle line:84%
about the accuracy
of cooperation

00:40:53.640 --> 00:40:56.880 align:middle line:84%
and how deeply it's
embedded into the world,

00:40:56.880 --> 00:40:59.280 align:middle line:84%
we need look no further
than the 50 trillion cells

00:40:59.280 --> 00:41:02.470 align:middle line:84%
we have in our bodies to see
that cooperation playing out.

00:41:02.470 --> 00:41:05.670 align:middle line:84%
So the key, what we
shared with the UN,

00:41:05.670 --> 00:41:07.440 align:middle line:90%
what we share in our teachings?

00:41:07.440 --> 00:41:08.580 align:middle line:90%
Look to nature.

00:41:08.580 --> 00:41:12.760 align:middle line:84%
Look to life for the model, and
apply that to our solutions.

00:41:12.760 --> 00:41:14.850 align:middle line:84%
And I think if we do
that, we can't go wrong.

00:41:14.850 --> 00:41:16.558 align:middle line:84%
>>LIPTON: I agree with
you, and I thank--

00:41:16.558 --> 00:41:17.683 align:middle line:90%
>>BRADEN: Dr. Bruce Lipton.

